featured_reviews.review_id:
I was visiting my fiance in Seattle, and we saw this store online and thought it sounded like fun so we went to check it out. I'm definitely never going to a chain store again! This place has the most insanely awesome selection of BDSM-type items I've ever seen in a store, all beautifully handmade, and almost all LOCALLY made! Everything is skillfully handcrafted, and I love that it's a small locally owned store that sources from local artists.

The owner, Lisa, was absolutely fantastic. I fell in love with a necklace that was quite pricey, we decided to splurge -- but she actually was so excited someone wanted to buy it, since it'd been taking up shelf space for so long, she cut the price for us. Definitely a great way to give a customer a good first experience. We also told her about a disappointing experience with the WeVibe, and she adamantly said that if she had been the one to sell it to us, she would have taken care of it -- the other store didn't. She talked us into considering the WeVibe 4 Plus, and when we decided to get it she even gave us a little discount as an apology for bad service that wasn't even her fault.

Unbelievably nice staff, fantastic selection, and mostly locally sourced? Yes please! I'm never going to another shop, this is the winner for me. Can't recommend it more, looking forward to a return visit.

I carry a backpack around with me because I don't own a car so it's essentially a bag for me to store things like backup battery, phone charger and such, headphones etc... a couple times I've gone to Doghouse Leathers I've been asked to leave the backpack behind the counter, and other times I've been the one asking if I need to leave it behind the counter depending on who is working.

Today there was someone who seemed like the manager or owner along with two pups in boy scouts uniforms, the pups were going about their business while when I entered I was greeted by the guy in the black harness and asked to leave my backpack behind the counter or if I was just picking something up at the counter I could leave it on. The way he went about saying it made me feel unwelcome and has left a bad taste in my mouth.

As much as I want to support a local business this makes me just want to shop on Amazon to avoid feeling singled out like this. I sincerely hope this is a misunderstanding but it certainly did not feel that way. Disappointed to leave this review.

Yes, we ask for bags to be checked at the front counter, and unfortunately will continue to do so for the time being, until which time our community and staff decide otherwise.
